        genes involved in the heat-shock response or those required
        for sporulation in 
        <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">Bacillus subtilis</ENAMEX> [ <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">7 8</NUMEX> ] .
        Identifying a differentially expressed sigma factor can
        provide a means to identifying other differentially
        expressed genes - genes whose expression are controlled by
        the sigma factor. To identify sigma factor-regulated genes,
        we developed a method, termed <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC">I-TRAP</ENAMEX>, for the 
